summary: Mark has been a constant through all my fandoms over the years and the reason I gave SPN a watch...whatever his next step is...
body:
Mark has been a constant through all my fandoms over the years and the reason I gave SPN a watch…whatever his next step is I’ll be watching Him!

Sounds like a Police song….

A “brand new character” yet he’s “reuniting with old friends”. Old friends could mean directors and writers he’s worked with before, old friends could mean castmates from old shows who are all embarking on a new show together.

I know we would all love to see him as Crowley again or back on SPN again but I am not getting my hopes up for that, given how he left the show, even though he did hashtag it SPNfamily. Maybe Fergus or maybe The Empty but…hmmm..im not going down that road and getting any kind of hopes up.

I’m very intrigued to see what this turns out to be!

title: Shield of Heaven
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2CKUKvS

by MalMuses

300 years after the Apocalypse, North America is a horrific parody of a bygone era; regressed technologically and near-constantly at war. The survivors are terrorized by their oppressors: Sam and Dean Winchester. Trapped as Lucifer’s Generals on Earth since the final seal broke, they remember nothing of who they were or what brought them here.

Before the Light Bringer returns to lead his final charge, the long-forgotten prophet Chuck Shurley starts a ripple effect that he hopes will change everything. He entrusts a demon with his plan to save the world—gaining his assistance to help throw an unwitting angel into the path of General Dean Winchester, the scourge of Chicago.

Enslaved and tortured at Dean’s hands and finally about to give up, Castiel can’t shake the feeling that he knew the man, once.

From his seat up in Detroit, the soulless General Sam Winchester gets wind of changes in the air; ones he’ll sacrifice anything—or anyone—to stop coming to pass.

When Dean’s world crashes down around him, Dean and Castiel are thrown together against an unknown enemy. With Chuck and Crowley carefully pulling the strings, Dean and Castiel plan to change everything—starting with each other.

He entrusts a demon with his plan to save the world—gaining his assistance to help throw an unwitting angel into the path of General Dean Winchester, the scourge of Chicago.

Enslaved and tortured at Dean’s hands and finally about to give up, Castiel can’t shake the feeling that he knew the man, once.

From his seat up in Detroit, the soulless General Sam Winchester gets wind of changes in the air; ones he’ll sacrifice anything—or anyone—to stop coming to pass.

When Dean’s world crashes down around him, Dean and Castiel are thrown together against an unknown enemy. With Chuck and Crowley carefully pulling the strings, Dean and Castiel plan to change everything—starting with each other.

tags: this was totally inspired by stumbling across neilman's picture of Hell's motivational posters again
summary: Motivational posters are absolutely something both Crowley and Aziraphale chalk up as a win for their respective side. To...
body:
Motivational posters are absolutely something both Crowley and Aziraphale chalk up as a win for their respective side. To inspire humans to be better is pretty much Aziraphale’s job description as heavenly agent on Earth, something to remind them to strive to be better by themselves surely has to be of heavenly origin!
But, oh, Crowley smirks when merely thinking about the frustration these bland phrases will cause, the envy for a better paid job they will invoke when being spotted in a superior’s office, the despair at being stuck at a dull and joyless job…the possibilities are sheer endless and all of them deliciously evil.
After he sees the ones Hell decided to produce for their own offices, he visits the angel’s bookshop with several bottles of wine under his arm. They get very drunk together while Crowley laments his (once considered brilliant by himself) invention of Comic Sans.
At least with the font, angel and demon agree on who is responsible for it.
